            <h2 class="about-project-title"><i>About Our Project</i></h2>
            <section class="project-overview">
                <p class="about-project">
                    This application is designed to evaluate ChatGPT’s performance in answering multiple-choice questions across various domains such as History, Social Science, and Computer Security. The app retrieves questions from a MongoDB database, sends them to ChatGPT using the OpenAI API, records the AI’s responses along with response times, and stores the results back into the database. It also includes middleware to validate query inputs, WebSocket integration for live progress updates, and API endpoints to retrieve evaluation metrics in real time. The project demonstrates full-stack development, server-client communication, and the integration of AI-driven evaluation within a web application.
